text: ONS data shows huge falls in non-Covid causes of death in December 2020.
The ONS has registered 4,122 deaths in 2020 due to Covid-19.
There was a large rise in the number of Covid deaths on 2 February 2022.
A chart titled Major Events in USA History that Cause Major Death Tolls and 2019 Data provides figures about COVID-19 deaths that are accurate as of May 23 2020.
The ONS have estimated that the restrictions across 2020 will have resulted in 200,000 non-Covid excess deaths.
The number of COVID-19 deaths recorded so far in 2021 has surpassed the total for 2020.
The number of people who have died in the U.S. in 2020 is on par with years prior to COVID-19.
Just 2.9% of deaths were caused by Covid-19 in the first three months of 2020.
A CNN chyron indicated that COVID-19's global death toll was approaching three million people on April 26 2020, transposing the rate of reported cases with the rate of deaths worldwide.
A meme accurately reports that the U.S. recorded roughly 2.9 million deaths in 2020 — almost the same total as previous years — despite COVID-19.
More people died of suicide in 2020 than died of COVID-19.
More than twice as many people died of Covid-19 in July and August 2022 than in the same months in 2021 and 2020.
